<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="051" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Ribbon + Command-Bar Launchers — Matter / Project / Account / Contact entity forms</title>
    <phase>Phase 5: Surfaces + Templates</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>050</dependencies>
    <blocks>060, 061, 062, 063</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, ribbon, frontend</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies ribbon XML and TypeScript code that wires user-visible launch points across four entity forms; touches solution ribbon DOM (high-blast-radius if wrong); tags include dataverse + ribbon</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Depends on task 050 (URL contract must exist); modifies shared ribbon XML resource; single critical-path task within the Phase 5 Surfaces sub-group.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add ribbon + command-bar buttons on `sprk_matter`, `sprk_project`, `account`, and `contact` entity forms (and their respective home-grid command bars) that open SpaarkeAi as a side pane (`Xrm.App.sidePanes`) pre-populated with the record's `ChatLaunchContext` (entity logical name + record id + `surfaceHint: 'sidePane'`). The ribbon XML lives in a `Communication`-style ribbon solution (use the `ribbon-edit` skill); the form-script glue lives in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/` extending the existing `EntityFormLaunch.ts` pattern with a new `openAsSidePane` export. The buttons are labeled "Open Spaarke AI" with the Spaarke logo icon and appear in the form command bar's "Collaborate" or "Tools" group (placement decided per entity convention).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Dataverse customization engineer with deep familiarity with ribbon XML (`RibbonDiffXml`, `CommandDefinitions`, `Actions`, `JavaScriptFunction`), web resource invocation, the `Xrm.App.sidePanes` API (vs `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo`), and Spaarke's ribbon convention of invocation-only scripts (ADR-006). You preserve the existing `openFromEntityForm` ribbon binding while adding the new side-pane binding.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **Ribbon XML changes** — `RibbonDiffXml` additions for `sprk_matter` (form + home grid), `sprk_project`, `account`, `contact` entities adding the "Open Spaarke AI" button with `Sprk.SpaarkeAi.EntityFormLaunch.openAsSidePane` as the function name. Buttons placed in the "Collaborate" or "Tools" group (consistent with existing Spaarke ribbon placements).
    2. **Form-script extension** — extend `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/EntityFormLaunch.ts` with `openAsSidePane(primaryControl: Xrm.FormContext)`. It extracts entity context, builds a `ChatLaunchContext` (with `surfaceHint: 'sidePane'`), and calls a new `openSpaarkeAiAsSidePane(ctx)` helper in `launch-resolver.ts` that uses `Xrm.App.sidePanes.createPane(...)` to mount SpaarkeAi as a 480px-wide side pane pre-populated with the context.
    3. **Backward compatibility** — the existing `openFromEntityForm` (which opens as a modal dialog) is preserved unchanged so that existing ribbon bindings (if any) continue to work. The new function is additive.

    Deliverable: ribbon XML diff in the solution's `customizations.xml` (deployed via the `ribbon-edit` skill workflow), edited `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/EntityFormLaunch.ts`, edited `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts` (adds `openSpaarkeAiAsSidePane`), and unit tests at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/__tests__/EntityFormLaunch.test.ts`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-14 mandates ribbon launchers on Matter, Project, Account, Contact entity forms that pre-populate `ChatLaunchContext` and open SpaarkeAi as a side pane. Design.md §4.5.2 lists "Command bar / ribbon Assistant button" as one of the seven Assistant host contexts; design.md §4.5.4 documents that **entity context** changes the agent's runtime behavior (playbook selected from `sprk_aichatcontextmap`, narrower tool set, system prompt knows "you are helping with this specific record").

      The existing `EntityFormLaunch.openFromEntityForm` opens SpaarkeAi as a **modal dialog** (target: 2). This task adds `openAsSidePane` which uses `Xrm.App.sidePanes.createPane(...)` instead — a different host context that keeps the form visible (split-screen UX) and is the recommended pattern for Action Engine entity-form invocation (design.md §4.5.4 "Entity context" row).

      Ribbon XML placement convention: Matter and Project use a "Tools" group on the form command bar; Account and Contact use the "Collaborate" group. Verify in the existing solution layout before adding. Use the `ribbon-edit` skill to extract → edit → repack → import, which is the canonical Spaarke workflow for ribbon changes.

      ADR-006: ribbon scripts are invocation-only — they extract context from `PrimaryControl` and delegate to a resolver module. No business logic, no URL construction, no direct Xrm.Navigation calls in `EntityFormLaunch.ts`. That contract MUST be preserved.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/EntityFormLaunch.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/WorkspaceLaunch.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/__tests__/EntityFormLaunch.test.ts</file>
      <file>infra/solutions/spaarke-action-engine-ribbon/customizations.xml</file>
      <file>infra/solutions/spaarke-action-engine-ribbon/solution.xml</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">Ribbon scripts are invocation-only. `EntityFormLaunch.ts` MUST NOT construct URLs, call `Xrm.Navigation` directly, or contain business logic. All such logic lives in `launch-resolver.ts`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">Vite + singlefile + React 19 build target. New TypeScript files compile to the existing single-file bundle. No new external dependencies.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 only. The side-pane host loads the existing SpaarkeAi shell which is already Fluent v9 compliant; this task adds no new UI surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use the `ribbon-edit` skill for solution export → ribbon XML edit → repack → import. Do NOT hand-edit the solution ZIP.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Preserve existing `openFromEntityForm` modal binding for backward compatibility. The new `openAsSidePane` is additive.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Button placement: Matter + Project → "Tools" group; Account + Contact → "Collaborate" group (verify against existing solution layout; deviate only with documented rationale).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Side pane width: 480px (matches Spaarke's existing side-pane conventions per `docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md`). Side pane title: the record's primary name + " — Spaarke AI".</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/plugins.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/entity-operations.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/ribbon-edit/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/pcf.md</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md</file>
