    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Ribbon invocation-only scripts" location="src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/EntityFormLaunch.ts">Existing `openFromEntityForm` extracts context from `PrimaryControl` and delegates to `launch-resolver.ts`. Follow the same shape for `openAsSidePane`.</pattern>
      <pattern name="ribbon-edit workflow" location=".claude/skills/ribbon-edit/SKILL.md">Solution export → unzip → edit `customizations.xml` `RibbonDiffXml` → repack → import. Always verify with the skill rather than hand-editing.</pattern>
      <pattern name="Xrm.App.sidePanes" location="docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md">Use `createPane({paneId, title, width, hideHeader, imageSrc})` then `pane.navigate(...)` to load the SpaarkeAi web resource into the pane.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, dependencies (task 050) marked ✅ in `TASK-INDEX.md`, and `ChatLaunchContext` type exists at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/ChatLaunchContext.ts`. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;` — especially the `ribbon-edit` skill's workflow, the existing `EntityFormLaunch.ts` shape, and design.md §4.5.4 (surface-context awareness).</step>
    <step order="2">Add `openSpaarkeAiAsSidePane(ctx: ChatLaunchContext)` to `launch-resolver.ts`: builds the URL via `buildLaunchUrl(ctx)`, calls `Xrm.App.sidePanes.createPane({title, width: 480, hideHeader: false, imageSrc: 'sprk_spaarke_logo_16'})` then `pane.navigate({pageType: 'webresource', webresourceName: 'sprk_spaarkeai', data: builtUrl})`. Fall back gracefully if `Xrm.App` is unavailable (warn + no-op, mirroring existing `openSpaarkeAi`).</step>
    <step order="3">Add `openAsSidePane(primaryControl: Xrm.FormContext)` to `EntityFormLaunch.ts`. Extract `entityLogicalName` + `entityId` from `primaryControl.data.entity`; build a `ChatLaunchContext` with `surfaceHint: 'sidePane'`; delegate to `openSpaarkeAiAsSidePane`. No URL construction in this file.</step>
    <step order="4">Author ribbon XML using the `ribbon-edit` skill. Export the target solution (or a small dedicated ribbon-extensions solution per Spaarke convention); edit `RibbonDiffXml` for `sprk_matter` (form + home grid), `sprk_project`, `account`, `contact` to add a `CommandDefinition` invoking `Sprk.SpaarkeAi.EntityFormLaunch.openAsSidePane` (library: `$webresource:sprk_spaarkeai_entityformlaunch`, with `&lt;CrmParameter Value="PrimaryControl"/&gt;`); add a matching `Button` in the correct group ("Tools" for Matter/Project, "Collaborate" for Account/Contact) with `LabelText="Open Spaarke AI"` and the Spaarke logo `Image16by16` + `Image32by32` references.</step>
    <step order="5">Repack the solution via the `ribbon-edit` workflow; import into the dev environment via `dataverse-deploy` (or the skill's own deploy step); verify the button appears on each of the four entity forms.</step>
    <step order="6">Create unit tests at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/__tests__/EntityFormLaunch.test.ts`: mock `Xrm.App.sidePanes.createPane` + the returned `pane.navigate` and verify (a) `openAsSidePane` extracts entity context correctly, (b) the resulting URL includes `surfaceHint=sidePane`, (c) the existing `openFromEntityForm` regression test still passes (no behavior change).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm test --workspace=src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` — all tests pass. Run `npm run build:prod --workspace=src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` — build succeeds. Deploy the updated web resource via the `code-page-deploy` skill if not already covered by step 5.</step>
    <step order="8">**Manual smoke test** (deferred — covered by `&lt;ui-tests&gt;` section): open a Matter record, click "Open Spaarke AI" in the ribbon, verify the side pane mounts at 480px with SpaarkeAi loaded and the matter's entity context populated.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` with progress; checkpoint via `context-handoff` skill.</step>
    <step order="9.5">**Quality gates** (FULL rigor): run `code-review` on `EntityFormLaunch.ts` + `launch-resolver.ts` + the ribbon XML diff (citing ADR-006 invocation-only contract); run `adr-check` (verify ADR-006, ADR-021, ADR-026 compliance — no business logic in ribbon scripts, Fluent v9 only, singlefile bundle preserved).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 051 status ✅. Update `current-task.md`: task 051 complete; unblocks Phase 6 integration tests.</step>
    <step order="11">If any deviations from this plan, document in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/051-deviations.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="ribbon-edit">Canonical Spaarke workflow for ribbon XML changes (export → edit → repack → import)</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Deploy the updated solution containing the ribbon changes</tool>
    <tool name="code-page-deploy">Deploy the updated SpaarkeAi web resource (for the new TypeScript)</tool>
    <tool name="npm">Run tests and production build</tool>
    <tool name="git">Confirm state</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ribbon/EntityFormLaunch.ts (edited — adds `openAsSidePane`)</output>
