    <output type="docs">projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/current-task.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">The "Open Spaarke AI" button appears on the `sprk_matter` form command bar (Tools group) when the dev solution is imported. Verified by manual smoke + `ui-test`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The same button appears on `sprk_project`, `account`, and `contact` forms (in their respective groups). Verified by manual smoke + `ui-test`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Clicking the button mounts SpaarkeAi as an `Xrm.App.sidePanes` pane at 480px width with the record's entity context populated in the URL. Verified by `ui-test`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The URL passed to the side pane contains `entityLogicalName`, `entityId`, and `surfaceHint=sidePane`. Verified by unit test mocking `Xrm.App.sidePanes`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The existing `openFromEntityForm` modal-dialog behavior is unchanged — regression test passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`EntityFormLaunch.ts` contains NO URL construction, NO direct `Xrm.Navigation` calls, NO business logic — ADR-006 compliance verified by `code-review`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build:prod --workspace=src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` exits 0; no new TypeScript errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new npm dependencies added.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Ribbon XML diff was authored via the `ribbon-edit` skill (not hand-edited ZIP) — verified by skill invocation record.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Button visible on Matter form (Tools group)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=entityrecord&amp;etn=sprk_matter</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Navigate to any Matter record</step>
        <step>Locate the form command bar; expand the "Tools" group if collapsed</step>
        <step>Verify "Open Spaarke AI" button is visible with the Spaarke logo icon</step>
        <step>Check browser console for JavaScript errors during form load</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Button renders with correct label + icon; no console errors.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Side pane opens with entity context (deep-link flow)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=entityrecord&amp;etn=sprk_matter</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open a Matter record</step>
        <step>Click "Open Spaarke AI" in the ribbon</step>
        <step>Verify a side pane opens at 480px width on the right side of the screen</step>
        <step>Verify the side pane title includes the matter's primary name</step>
        <step>Open browser dev tools; verify the side pane's iframe URL contains `entityLogicalName=sprk_matter`, `entityId={matter-guid}`, and `surfaceHint=sidePane`</step>
        <step>Verify the SpaarkeAi shell renders inside the pane with no console errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Side pane opens with the correct width, title, URL params, and rendered shell. No console errors.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Button visible on Account, Contact, Project forms (Collaborate / Tools group)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=entityrecord&amp;etn=account</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Navigate to an Account record; verify "Open Spaarke AI" appears in the "Collaborate" group</step>
        <step>Navigate to a Contact record; verify "Open Spaarke AI" appears in the "Collaborate" group</step>
        <step>Navigate to a Project record; verify "Open Spaarke AI" appears in the "Tools" group</step>
        <step>Click the button on each and verify side pane opens with the entity's logical name + id</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All three forms have the button in the correct group; clicking each opens the side pane with correct context.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode in D365 user settings</step>
        <step>Open a Matter record; click "Open Spaarke AI"</step>
        <step>Verify the side pane content (SpaarkeAi shell) renders correctly in dark mode — no white backgrounds, no black-on-black text, icons use `currentColor`</step>
        <step>Verify the ribbon button icon adapts to dark mode (or remains legibly visible)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Side pane content respects Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens per ADR-021; no contrast failures.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    The exact ribbon group placement ("Tools" vs "Collaborate") MUST be verified against the target environment's existing ribbon layout before authoring the diff. If a group does not exist for a given entity, place the button at the top level of the command bar (not the form's `Mscrm.Form` overflow menu).

    For the home-grid command bar (Matter list view), the button should appear when no records or single records are selected. Selection-based behavior (multi-record selection) is deferred — only single-record / no-selection invocation is in MVP scope.

    The Spaarke logo icon web resource (`sprk_spaarke_logo_16`, `sprk_spaarke_logo_32`) MUST exist in the environment. If absent, deploy via the standard Spaarke shared-assets solution before importing this ribbon diff.

    Do NOT remove or modify `openFromEntityForm` — it is the modal-dialog binding used by other Spaarke surfaces.

    The `Xrm.App.sidePanes` API requires Unified Interface; classic UI is not supported. Spaarke is UCI-only so this is acceptable; document the constraint in the function's TSDoc.
  </notes>

